Reasoning: The paper discusses criteria for non-mechanical intelligence and proposes variations of the Turing Test for use in MMORPGs and virtual reality systems. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The practical applications of the tests also suggest a connection to cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of Second Life as a framework for implementing the tests suggests a connection to graphics (cs.GR).
